items.title: John Bolton indicted by grand jury, latest Trump foe to face criminal charges
items.description: FBI agents on Aug. 22 raided John Bolton's Maryland home and office in Washington, D.C., as part of a criminal investigation.

items.title: U.S. Chamber of Commerce sues Trump administration over $100,000 H-1B visa fee
items.description: Trump recently imposed a $100,00 fee on temporary visas for highly skilled workers in a push to have American companies hire more domestic workers.

items.title: Bill to fund military during government shutdown fails in Senate procedural vote
items.description: Democrats largely voted against the bill to fund the Pentagon amid the shutdown. The vote came hours after a Senate bill to fund the entire government...

items.title: Trump says he and Putin will meet in Hungary to discuss war in Ukraine
items.description: President Donald Trump this week said that he is considering sending Tomahawk missiles to Ukraine to ratchet up pressure on Russia to end the war.

items.title: Illinois Gov. JB Pritzker won $1.4 million gambling last year, tax filings show
items.description: Pritzker has become a leading antagonist of President Donald Trump over federal immigration operations in Chicago and elsewhere.
